Creating Images with R

With a little bit of magick

Melinda Courtney

2023-03-11

My Meme

I created my meme because my flatmate showed me a version of the same meme a few days ago, and I was reminded of how brilliant it was. What makes my meme original is that I came up with text that is more relevant to me.

My Meme

library(magick)
library(tidyverse)

#Square One
lecture_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                            height = 500, 
                            color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "You were not at\nthe lecture",
                 color = "#ffffff",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Geneva",
                 gravity = "center")

#Square Two
recording_text <- image_blank(width = 500,
                              height = 500, 
                              color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I watched\nthe recording",
                 color = "#ffffff",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Geneva",
                 gravity = "center")

#Square Three
mad_lady <- image_read("http://hollywoodlife.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/kyle-richards-taylor-armstrong-rhobh-bravo-ftr.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)

#Square Four
cat <- image_read("https://nftevening.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Untitled-design-7-1.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)


#Making the rows

#Top Row
text_vector <- c(lecture_text, recording_text)
top_row <- image_append(text_vector)

#Bottom Row
image_vector <- c(mad_lady, cat)
bottom_row <- image_append(image_vector)

#Putting them together
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack=TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(500)

meme

image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My Animated GIF

I created my GIF because I spent the weekend with my brother playing a video game called Go Vacation that we played as kids and I decided to make a GIF out of the different maps available to play on. Its original because barely anyone has heard of the game, let alone made a GIF out of the maps.

My Animated GIF

library(magick)

marine_image <- image_read("https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vv84LpyWO64/maxresdefault.jpg") %>%
  image_scale (500)

city_image <- image_read("https://i0.wp.com/tiredoldhack.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/go-vacation-pic6.jpg?ssl=1") %>%
  image_scale (500)

mountain_image <- image_read("https://laurasambitiouswriting.files.wordpress.com/2018/06/govacationphoto.png?w=825") %>%
  image_scale (500)

snow_image <- image_read("https://i0.wp.com/ladiesgamers.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2018072919015500-F64836112794B38AB195F3CAD1E2E9E6.jpg?resize=900%2C400&ssl=1") %>%
  image_scale (500)
  
vacation_image <- image_read("https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0mn34hThWBI/maxresdefault.jpg") %>%
  image_scale (500)
  


  # Create Frame 1
  frame1 <- marine_image %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Marine Resort",
                   size = 60,
                   color = "#ffffff",
                   gravity = "north") %>%
    image_scale(500)%>%
    image_extent("500x500")
  
  frame2 <- city_image %>%
    image_annotate(text = "City Resort",
                   size = 60,
                   color = "#ffffff",
                   gravity = "north") %>%
    image_scale(500)%>%
    image_extent("500x500")
  
  frame3 <- mountain_image %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Mountain Resort",
                   size = 60,
                   color = "#ffffff",
                   gravity = "north") %>%
    image_scale(500)%>%
    image_extent("500x500")
  

  frame4 <- snow_image %>%
    image_annotate(text = "Snow Resort",
                   size = 60,
                   color = "#ffffff",
                   gravity = "north")%>%
    image_scale(500)%>%
    image_extent("500x500")
  
  frame5 <- vacation_image%>%
    image_annotate(text = "Start your own Adventure",
                   size = 40,
                   color = "#ffffff",
                   gravity = "south")%>%
    image_scale(500)%>%
    image_extent("500x500")
  
  #putting the frames in order
  frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5)
  
  #Putting the frames together
  animation<- image_animate (frames, fps = 1)
  
  animation
  
  image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
